File: Singer Lady Gaga performs during the Hurricane Relief concert in College Station, Texas, on October 21, 2017. JOHANNESBURG - The World Health Organization and Global Citizen are teaming up to hold a concert of epic proportions. The concert is being held under the theme, One World: Together At Home. International stars like Lady Gaga, Jennifer Lopez, Sam Smith, Alicia Keys and Taylor Swift will perform. READ: Celine Dion salutes 'heroic' workers in pandemic fight Our very own Black Coffee, Sho Madjozi, Cassper Nyovest and Nomzamo Mbatha will also be part of the event. The concert aims to support and applaud health workers on the frontline of the fight against COVID-19. Over 2 million cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed globally with more than 150 000 deaths. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.